## Improved README.md

**Project Overview**

This project provides a web proxy that can be used to bypass CORS restrictions and access resources from other domains. The proxy is designed to be compatible with Vercel and other static serverless sites.

**Usage**

To use the proxy, you can send a request to the following URL:

```
https://<your-proxy-url>/<target-url>
```

For example, to access the `https://example.com` website, you would send a request to the following URL:

```
https://<your-proxy-url>/https://example.com
```

**Dependencies**

The following dependencies are required to run the proxy:

- Node.js
- Express
- Axios

**Known Bugs and Limitations**

The proxy is currently unable to handle requests that require authentication.

**Contributing**

Contributions are welcome! Please read the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md) before submitting a pull request.

## Explanations

**api/nodemon.json**

The `nodemon.json` file is used to configure the following settings:

- `watch`: This property specifies which files to watch for changes. The `*.js` pattern matches all JavaScript files, the `public/*` pattern matches all files in the `public` directory, and the `utils/*` pattern matches all files in the `utils` directory.
- `ignore`: This property specifies which directories to ignore. The `node_modules` directory is ignored because it contains dependencies that are not necessary to watch for changes.
- `ext`: This property specifies which file extensions to watch for changes. The `js,html,css` pattern matches all JavaScript, HTML, and CSS files.

**package.json**

```json
{
  "name": "web-proxy",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "A web proxy that can be used to bypass CORS restrictions and access resources from other domains.",
  "main": "app.js",
  "dependencies": {
    "axios": "^0.21.1",
    "express": "^4.17.1",
    "logger": "^0.0.1"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "mocha": "^9.2.2"
  }
}
```

The `package.json` file contains the following information:

- `name`: The name of the project.
- `version`: The version of the project.
- `description`: The description of the project.
- `main`: The main entry point of the project.
- `dependencies`: The dependencies of the project.
- `devDependencies`: The development dependencies of the project.

**app.test.js**

```js
const app = require('../app');
const request = require('supertest');

describe('web-proxy', () => {
  it('should proxy GET requests', async () => {
    const response = await request(app).get('/https://example.com');
    expect(response.status).toBe(200);
  });
});
```

The `app.test.js` file contains the unit tests for the proxy.

## New Files

**utils/request.js**

```js
const axios = require('axios');

module.exports = async (url) => {
  try {
    const response = await axios.get(url);
    return response.data;
  } catch (error) {
    throw error;
  }
};
```

The `utils/request.js` file contains a simple utility function that is used to make HTTP requests.

## Improvements to api/nodemon.json

The following improvements have been made to the `api/nodemon.json` file:

- The `watch` property has been expanded to include all JavaScript, HTML, CSS, and utility files.
- The `ignore` property has been expanded to include all directories in the `node_modules` directory and the `.git` directory.

These improvements will ensure that the proxy is able to watch for changes to all of the files that it needs to in order to function properly.